|succession      = [[Empress consort of Japan]]
|reign           = 31 May 1190 – 9 August 1200
|consort         = yes
|spouse          = {{marriage|[[Emperor Go-Toba]]|1190}}
|issue           = [[Princess Shōshi (1195–1211)|Princess Shōshi]]
|royal house     = [[Imperial House of Japan]]
|father          = [[Fujiwara no Kanezane|Kujō Kanezane]]
|mother          = Fujiwara no Tomoko
|birth_date      = 31 October 1173
|birth_place     =
|death_date      = {{death date and age|1239|2|3|1173|10|31|df=yes}}
|death_place     = Heian-kyō (Kyōto)
|burial_date     =
|burial_place    =
|}}

{{nihongo|'''Kujō Ninshi'''|九条 任子||31 October 1173 – 3 February 1239}}, also known as {{nihongo|'''Fujiwara no Ninshi'''|藤原 任子}} was an [[empress consort of Japan]]. She was the consort of [[Emperor Go-Toba]].

She was the daughter of [[Sessho|regent]] [[Kujō Kanezane]].

Upon the death of her mother in 1201, she [[Buddhist initiation ritual|undertook the Buddhist precepts]] under the monk [[Hōnen]]. 

;Issue:

* Imperial Princess ''[[Princess Shōshi (1195–1211) |Shōshi]]'' (昇子内親王) (1195–1211) - unmarried Empress as adopted mother of Emperor Juntoku (Shunkamon-in, 春華門院)

==Notes==
