{{nihongo|'''Kujō Ninshi'''|九条 任子||31 October 1173 – 3 February 1239}}, also known as {{nihongo|'''Fujiwara no Ninshi'''|藤原 任子}} was an [[empress consort of Japan]]. She was the consort of [[Emperor Go-Toba]].

She was the daughter of [[Sessho|regent]] [[Kujō Kanezane]].

Upon the death of her mother in 1201, she [[Buddhist initiation ritual|undertook the Buddhist precepts]] under the monk [[Hōnen]]. 

