{{nihongo|'''Kujō Ninshi'''|九条 任子||31 October 1173 – 3 February 1239}}, also known as {{nihongo|'''Fujiwara no Ninshi'''|藤原 任子}} was an {{ill|Empress of Japan|en|Empress of Japan|qid=Q595038|lt=Empress of Japan|1=Empress of Japan}}. She was the consort of {{ill|Emperor Go-Toba|en|Emperor Go-Toba|qid=Q316658|lt=Emperor Go-Toba|1=Emperor Go-Toba}}.

She was the daughter of [[:en:Sessho|regent]] [[:en:Kujō Kanezane|Kujō Kanezane]].

Upon the death of her mother in 1201, she [[:en:Buddhist initiation ritual|undertook the Buddhist precepts]] under the monk {{ill|Hōnen|en|Hōnen|qid=Q507980|lt=Hōnen|1=Hōnen}}. 

;Issue:

* Imperial Princess ''{{ill|Princess Shōshi (1195–1211) |en|Princess Shōshi (1195–1211) |qid=Q15614112|lt=Shōshi|1=Princess Shōshi (1195–1211)}}'' (昇子内親王) (1195–1211) - unmarried Empress as adopted mother of Emperor Juntoku (Shunkamon-in, 春華門院)

